drive
Homonym Number: 4
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the shifting of a mob of sheep by driving, mainly from the point of view of the animals driven (`a drove'), but also from that of the action of driving (`a short drive').
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
